<font color="#FF0000">JUST SITTING THERE...</font><br>
<tt>Sat Jan 17  2:38:40 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
Doc Del,<br><br>
No, I have not got any regrets about this incident, because there was no way I could have changed it.  The decision was made way above me, by the powers-to-be, not to participate.  This was probably based upon the need to preserve our capabilities, some mission requirements, and the potential for hostile action during the rescue effort.  <br><br>
But, less than two years before, I participated in just such a rescue effort, and we evacuated 22 people during a flood from a island just before the island ceased to exist.  The difference--this rescue was in Korea, not Vietnam.<br><br>
Sitting there was not easy for us.  Not when we knew we could make a difference if given a chance.  Perhaps that incident could be a metiphore for the war as a whole.
<p><code>-- searat@sorcom.com  (John C. Ratliff) </code><p>


